[Although the source of this outbreak of _E. coli_ O157:H7 has yet to be
determined, the suspicion of a cheese made from unpasteurized milk once
again brings up the specter of diseases transmitted by dairy products
produced from this vehicle. - Mod.LL]
[In 1998 ProMED-mail reported on an outbreak of _E. coli_ O157 associated
with unpasteurized milk in the UK in 1998 (see refs below in see
also's). To further highlight the hazards of consumption of unpasteurized
dairy products, we have included prior ProMED-mail postings on a variety of
bacterial organisms related to unpasteurized dairy products. - Mod. MPP]
